{"questionId":"3394642","questionHtml":"<p>Two spaceships, X and Y move in opposite directions away from a space station. The speeds of the spaceships relative to the space station are <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math></em> and <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math></em>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/d75ec22ef5de249b60561b2e91f3dc911bd6fca9.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the speed of Y in the reference frame of X?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3394642","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.HL.TZ0.13","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Two spaceships, X and Y move in opposite directions away from a space station. The speeds of the spaceships relative to the space